section.sculpture-portfolioPage
  .container
    .row
      .col.l12.m12.s12#workSlideshow
        .carousel.carousel-slider.center(data-indicators='true')
          .carousel-item.white-text(href='#one!')
            img(src='/assets/imgs/portfolioWork/visualArt/sculpture/sidewayMirror/sidewayMirror.jpg')
          .carousel-item.white-text(href='#two!')
            img(src='/assets/imgs/portfolioWork/visualArt/sculpture/sidewayMirror/sidewayMirror2.jpg')

    .row
      .col.l1
        button.togglePortfolioCopy.waves-effect.waves-light
          i.fa.fa-chevron-up(aria-hidden='true')
      .col.l5.m2
        p#workSubHeading TOGGLE WORK DESCRIPTION
      .col.l1.m2.s4.offset-l5.offset-m3
        ul.center-align
          li#portfolioPageNext
            a(href='sculpture-templar.html')
              i.fa.fa-chevron-right(aria-hidden='true').right.waves-effect
    .row.portfolioCopy
      .col.l6.m6.s12
        h3.workTitle Sideway Mirror
        h6.push-leading.workSubHeading 2016
        p.workSubHeading SCULPTURE
          p.workDescription
            | With the artist still engage with what it the processes that an object undergoes
            | during its production into a final form, a process in which the artist argues is one
            | of the key insights into how this object obtains it's value. Aside from inherited context,
            | the objects in Sideway Mirror attempt a dialogue with each other, each of which were
            | used to build, or plan the next.
      .col.l1.m1.s1
        ul.center-align
          li#next
            a(href='sculpture-templar.html')
              i.fa.fa-chevron-right(aria-hidden='true').right.waves-effect
